<https://w3id.org/fair-metrics/general/FM_F1_M_IdentPersistent>
    a                          ftr:Metric, dcat:Dataset ;
    rdfs:definedBy            <https://fairmetrics.github.io/Metrics/metric/general/FM_F1_M_IdentPersistent.ttl> ;

    ftr:identifier            "https://w3id.org/fair-metrics/general/FM_F1_M_IdentPersistent"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title             "FAIR Metric - F1 - Metadata - Identifier is persistent" ;
    vivo:abbreviation         "FM_F1_M_IdentPersistent" ;
    dcat:landingPage          <https://w3id.org/fair-metrics/general/FM_F1_M_IdentPersistent> ;

    dcterms:description       """<p>This metric evaluates whether the identifier provided as input satisfies the EOSC-PID aligned [FAIRsharing definition](<a href="https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/record-sections-and-fields/general-information/globally-unique-persistent-and-resolvable-identifier-schemas)">https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/record-sections-and-fields/general-information/globally-unique-persistent-and-resolvable-identifier-schemas)</a> of persistence.</p>

<p>F1 requires that metadata be assigned a globally unique, persistent and resolvable identifier. This metric is particularly concerned with the persistence aspect of GUPRIs; persistence is required to guarantee long-term continuity of reference. Without persistence, identifiers may break, change or be reassigned, undermining citation, traceability and reproducibility.  In this metric, the definition of persistence follows the [FAIRsharing guidance](<a href="https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/record-sections-and-fields/general-information/globally-unique-persistent-and-resolvable-identifier-schemas)">https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/record-sections-and-fields/general-information/globally-unique-persistent-and-resolvable-identifier-schemas)</a> on Globally Unique, Persistent and Resolvable Identifier (GUPRI) schemas. This definition requires that the identifier schema must have clear community backing for the schema and its long-term maintenance. The syntax of the schema must be stable, and the referred object should itself should also be stable, though there are various ways to show this (e.g., a dataset might be completely immutable, while a record describing an organisation is likely to change as the organisations homepage, name or other attributes change). This metric evaluates whether the identifier provided as input is issued under a schema that meets the FAIRsharing definition of persistence. The evaluation assesses whether the identifier schema demonstrates documented long-term maintenance and governance consistent with these criteria.</p>

<p>For an in-depth understanding of the issues around identifiers, please see [<a href="http://dx.plos.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.2001414">http://dx.plos.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.2001414</a>](<a href="http://dx.plos.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.2001414).">http://dx.plos.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.2001414).</a> #</p>""" ;
    dcat:keyword              "FAIR", "F1", "identifier", "metadata" ;
dqv:inDimension <https://doi.org/10.25504/FAIRsharing.a2cea7> ;
    dcat:landingPage          <https://w3id.org/fair-metrics/general/FM_F1_M_IdentPersistent> ;

